modules.description: This module defines version metadata including a version string, optional commit hash, and optional commit date. It provides direct access to these values as module-level constants. Concrete use cases include embedding build information or tracking source control details for debugging and release management.

Handles in-memory modifications of file content by replacing specific line ranges and supports committing changes to disk with options to apply, fake, or diff the patch. Works with strings representing file paths and blocks of text, tracking changes in memory before writing. Useful for tools that need to modify source files programmatically, such as code refactoring utilities or automated patching systems.

This module manages version metadata and enables programmatic file content modifications with precise line replacements. It exposes version strings, commit hashes, and dates as constants, while providing operations to apply, simulate, or diff in-memory text patches. You can embed build information, track source control details, and modify source files by replacing specific line ranges before writing changes to disk. Example uses include automated patching, refactoring tools, and release tracking with embedded versioning.
